Bauchi – South Africa-based aviation consultants, SIATA Aviation, is to partner with Bauchi State Government to establish fly academy and research institute in the state. Briefing newsmen on Wednesday at the Government House, Bauchi, Capt. Ibrahim Sherif, the team leader, said they were also working in collaboration with Ambro Afrique consultants to realise the project in the state. “The establishment of fly academy and other projects is aimed at utilising the Bauchi international airport to generate revenue,” he said. “We will incorporate the research institute with Abubakar Tafawa Balewa University (ATBU) to train and create employment for the citizens of the state. Sherif, who said its team were in Bauchi for facility study, noted that the planned institute would also work with Yankari game reserve to boost the tourism potential of the state. “We will also establish manufacturing plant, and all these projects will be linked to aviation, with the aim of revenue generation for the state as well as creation of employment for the citizens to boost Nigeria’s economy. On how to inject funds in the project, Sherif said “funding of the project will be equity participation and return will be shared among investors and the state government. 0 comments Do you get a good or bad response from your wife after making love? Discover a great natural solution that changed my story and put an end to weak/premature ejaculation, CLICK HERE.  100% Natural Solution To Premature Ejaculation, Weak Erection, Watery Sperm, Other Sexual Dysfunctions And Last More Than 30 Minutes During Sex.